President Biden visited Joint Base Langley-Eustis in Virginia and delivered a speech expressing gratitude and admiration for the men and women serving in the military. He shared personal stories about his son Beau, who served in the military, and praised the sacrifices and dedication of military families. The President acknowledged the challenges faced by service members, including deployments and the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic. He highlighted the accomplishments of the U.S. Armed Forces in Afghanistan and emphasized the importance of supporting veterans and their families. President Biden also discussed the need to focus on future threats and rebuild capabilities to ensure the security of the American people. He concluded by expressing his deep appreciation for the service members and reaffirming his commitment as Commander-in-Chief.